Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_net_parasitics(25.10)                      report_net_parasitics(25.10)

Name
       report_net_parasitics - Reports the RC parasitics of the specified net

Syntax
        report_net_parasitics

       <net_name>

       [-help]

       -rc_corner <rc_corner_name>

       [-file_name <output_file_name>]

       Reports the RC parasitics of the specified net.

       The  report_net_parasitics  command  reports a list of attackers in the
       order of worst coupling capacitance by default. The software determines
       and reports the probable top N worst attackers for a victim.  The  com-
       mand  output  will  show  worst coupling capacitance, in addition to RC
       parasitics.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  report_net_parasitics parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the  man command:

               man report_net_parasitics

       -file_name <output_file_name>
              Specifies the name of the output file.

       -rc_corner <rc_corner_name>
              Specifies the RC corner name for which the RC parasitics are  to
              be reported.

       <net_name>
              Specifies the name of the net for which the RC parasitics are to
              be reported.

Example
              * The  following command reports the RC parasitics for net, NET1
                for RC corner, rc_best:

                report_net_parasitics -rc_corner rc_best NET1

                Net: NET1

                RC Corner: rc_best

                Total Cap = 0.473082 ff

                Total Res = 2.104041 ohms

                Total XCap = 0.334035 ff

                Cap Distribution:

                Total Ground Cap = 0.139046 ff

                 XCap With Nets:

                NET3 = 0.059964 ff

                 NET4 = 0.040277 ff

                 NET5 = 0.233794 ff

